News Coverage


May 2, 2017Bloomberg TV
Bloomberg TV interviews Alex Roepers on Japan's economy, corporate reforms, and activism in Japan at the Milken Conference in Los Angeles on May 2, 2017.



September 8, 2016Institutional Investors Alpha: Unhedged Commentary: Finding Value in Value Stocks
Investment styles tend to move in multiyear cycles. We believe U.S. equity markets recently passed an important inflection point, heralding a rotation back to value investing. This rotation started as a result of stabilizing macro conditions and because many value stocks had become too cheap to ignore, in both absolute and relative terms.



April 23, 2016Barron's: Forgotten FMC's Attractions
Though its stock has risen some during the market’s recent rally, FMC, a midsize chemicals firm, remains a forgotten underperformer. Alexander Roepers, Atlantic Investment Management’s president believes “the company has self-help levers that should improve EPS significantly by 2018 or earlier” The agricultural cycle could roll over again, but given how low the shares remain, the downside seems limited compared to the upside.



April 9, 2016At Owens-Illinois, the Glass Is Half-Full
Several insiders have been buying stock, a good sign. The new chief financial officer, Jan Bertsch, and three other officers picked up shares in February at prices ranging from $13 to $15 a share. The stock has also attracted a number of noted value investors, including Alexander Roepers’ Atlantic Investment Management...



March 9, 2016HFM Week: Behind Closed Doors - The "Friendly" Activists Keeping a Low Profile
“We are constructive and engaged with boards but we have two other objectives: to retain liquidity and to always remain respectful of management because it’s a small world, we have been doing this for a long time and we want to continue doing this for a long time,” says founder and CIO Roepers.



August 15, 2015Barron's: Owens-Illinois Glass Half Full
Beneath the surface of this battered company there are important changes that could brighten the picture by the end of 2016, avers Alexander Roepers, president of Atlantic Investment Management, which has been adding shares. Its 8% stake makes Atlantic one of the company’s largest holders.



April 10, 2015Wall Street Journal: Can Owens-Illinois Put the Genie Back in a Bottle?
Owens - Illinois finally seems to be on the mend, said Alexander Roepers, president of Atlantic Investment Management Inc., New York which owns about 7.5% of the bottle maker.



