Overview


Atlantic applies a business owner’s mindset in identifying its investments, conducting rigorous financial and operational due diligence, emphasizing predictability of cash flows and adhering to a strict buy/sell discipline. Atlantic takes significant minority ownership stakes in its portfolio companies and serves as a constructive shareholder, seeking to unlock value over time.  The strategies focus on undervalued companies that are temporarily out-of-favor and candidates for an earnings turnaround, restructuring or takeover.


Long-only Strategies
Atlantic’s long-only strategies take concentrated stakes in a limited number of high conviction longs within a carefully-defined universe of quality, mid-cap industrial and consumer companies in the U.S. and Globally. Atlantic uses its position as a significant minority investor in its portfolio companies to constructively engage with company management to unlock incremental value. The long-only strategies do not use options, leverage or futures.

Long/Short Strategies
Atlantic’s long/short strategies invest in quality, mid-cap industrial and consumer companies in the U.S., Europe, Japan, and Asia ex-Japan. Atlantic takes concentrated positions in a limited number of high-conviction longs and actively trades a diversified portfolio of shorts in overvalued or fundamentally challenged companies, while carefully managing net market exposure. The long portfolios consist of undervalued companies that are temporarily out-of-favor and candidates for an earnings turnaround, restructuring or takeover in the industrial and consumer products and services sectors. The strategies do not use leverage on its longs or futures, but may selectively use put options to enhance short positions or for market hedging purposes.






