Atlantic Investment Management

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Atlantic Investment Management





Type

Independent Investment Advisory Firm


Industry
Global Investment Management


Founded
1988[1][2]


Headquarters
666 Fifth Avenue, 34th Floor, New York, NY 10103
United States[3]



Area served

Worldwide



Key people

Alexander J. Roepers, Founder, President and Portfolio Manager


AUM
US $2.3 Billion[4]


Website
www.atlanticinvestment.net


Atlantic Investment Management is a global alternative investment firm founded in 1988 by Alexander J. Roepers (“Alex”).[3] Atlantic has 29 employees worldwide with offices in New York City and Tokyo.[5] As of June 2014, the firm had $2.3 billion in assets under management.[4]



